      "content": "exactly. and it's not just the telemetry. i was looking at some old declassified memos from the era and there's this weird pattern of budget reallocations to \"black site\" lunar observation projects right after the Apollo missions. if they were just looking at rocks, why the sudden massive shift in compartmentalized funding? can you help me figure out what kind of specific technical specs or signal frequencies might have been used to detect something that wouldn't be classified as \"natural\" topography?",
