      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. the gravimetric sensor idea is a big lead. if they were using those to look for something artificial, they'd have to hide the results in the most boring-looking datasets. i'm trying to cross-reference the Apollo 11 and 12 data streams with known seismic events from that time. do you think there's any way to predict which specific signal patterns would indicate a man-made structure versus just a moonquake? if i can find that pattern, i might be able to spot where they forced the \"reset\" in the data.",
